385.name: The Daniels Murder
385.description: This is the true story of Obory Daniels, a colonist who took issue with the law prohibiting children. He also took issue with the fact that the Council, a collection of the original colonists, chooses which DNA to use on new clones and kept the DNA secured away from others. Some colonists wanted to have family members restored, this was not possible. The council argued that there was no guarantee that the family members DNA would yield the same family member they once knew since the limiter implant would allow anyone to have the skills needed for the planet. The choices were simply made out of who they felt was best suited to survive on this new world. But Daniels Argued that there was no way to be certain until that DNA was allowed to try to survive on the planet, after all humans are very adaptable and durable creatures if nothing else.

386.name: The Formation of Freedomtown
386.description:
In the months following the murder of, and refusal to re-clone Obory Daniels, the citizens of Plymouth were beginning to notice the oppression of the council. Protests began in the town, led by an enigmatic young man named Edward Salazar. The protestors refused to work until Daniels was re-cloned and the ideas he proposed discussed.

To quell the rebellion the council created the first of a series of Cyborgs which they called Peacekeepers, which were integrated with brain wave inhibitors that made them completely loyal to the council.

1244.name: Freefall, by Dr. Farah Kapoor
1244.description:
The Northern Star floats in orbit above Rhyldan.

An interstellar tin can. A maze of corridors and airlocks and cramped rooms, and not one window with a view outside. A tangle of dark Terran-born alloys, all sharp edges, vertices and angles against the gleaming blue curve of the planet.

Two space-faring ecosystems, facing each other.

A tiny sliver of bright light shines across one of the metallic facets, like the parting of lips in a slow smile. A mechanic jaw lowers, widening the crack into a maw.

As red and blue beacons pulse inside, the Northern Star sighs a gust of its inner atmosphere. The deep cold of space bites and freezes all traces of moisture, weaving with them a subtle veil of arctic mist. Glittering frozen cobwebs swirl in the undercurrents of tracking beams that, with slow and gentle tugs, tow a little shuttle away from the ship.

1291.name: Motherless Manifesto, by Kumiko Loufaroo
1291.description:
In blood-drenched Plymouth, Year 16.


We are the Many.

The Siblings.

The Mutts, the Baked, the Motherless Cubs.

The Sons of Rhyldan; the Vat-Born.

Yet the purebred Crew would have us believe that they bear us in their womb.

Why?

We are the Motherless; our Mothers they are not.

And they are neither warm nor caring. Their worn masks cannot hide the arrogance of power.

We say: Hear us! and they say: You must obey.

Why?

We say: Teach us about Earth! and they say: We brought no History books on the Star.

Why?

It makes no sense!

Why would they be so eager to leave History behind?

We say: Let us decide!

They say: We know best.

Do they?

How?

What gives them the right to be right?

We protest, and in their good, caring wisdom they hurl the Peacekeepers and the Troops against us.

In their good, caring wisdom they drown our streets in our blood.

Our streets.

Our Mnemosyne blood.

Now they tell us: Stand down!

They tell us: Behave!

1677.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Lt. Danielle Decroux
1677.description:
Human Sniper.
First Landing Expedition.

Onboard: Security, 4th in command.

Rank: Lieutenant.

AKA: "Zedkay", for "Zero Kelvin" - Absolute cold.

French; GIGN officer; top percentile sniper. Small, compact, muscular, black hair.

Trained Gavin "Golem" Stones in long-range firearms.

Member of the First Expedition: Lt. Decroux is the first human to have set foot on Rhyldan.

"Aim for the heads." - Zedkay to Gavin, as they faced the First Lesoo Raid.

Status: Alive.

FTO: Fried Camembert (Food) with Beaujolais Wine (Beverage).

1678.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Lt. Rodrigo Souza
1678.description:
Human CQC.
First Landing Expedition.

Onboard: Security, 5th in command.

Rank: Lieutenant.

AKA: "Yaco", for "Yacar" (Alligator in Portuguese)

Brazilian; BOPE officer; twice ACDD champion. Tall, wiry, dark-skinned.

Trained Gavin "Golem" Stones in hand-to-hand combat.

During the Journey, the most cloned crewmember (10 times).

Member of the First Expedition: along Dr. Choi and Dr. Yamada, Lt. Souza is the fifth human to have set foot on Rhyldan.

"Beleza!" - Yaco, as he took off his helmet and breathed for the first time the Rhyldan air.

Status: Alive.

FTO: "No Woman, No Cry", by Robert Marley (Music).

1679.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Dr. Thomas ODoyle
1679.description:
Human MnemoTech.
Mnemosye Team; Neosyne Layer.

Onboard: Mnemosyne Team.

Rank: Doctor.

AKA: N/A.

Irish; Neuroscientist, Dublin Institute of Technology. Four times Nobel nominee.

Along Dr. Leticia Lopez and Dr. Ralf Hounds, layered Gavin "Golem" Stones.

"Just for once dont argue, my love. There is not enough room for us all." - Thomas to Letty, as he pushed her into the last escape pod.

Status: Starfell.

FTO: "The Picture of Dorian Gray", by Oscar Wilde (Book).

1680.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Laura Orouli
1680.description:
Mnemosyne Hacker.
First Siblings.

Onboard: Systems, unranked.

Rank: N/A.

AKA: "Runt"

The Third Mnemosyne; layered by Dr. Noora Hasanat & Dr. Zhelya Jamajami.

Sibling to Gavin "Golem" Stones and Faye "Mutt" Thomas. Trained in Systems by Mr. Gao Jianyu.

"Please, boys... dont fight!" - Laura, to Gavin and Faye, during the Quarrels.

Status: Alive.

1681.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Gavin Stones
1681.description:
Mnemosyne CQC.
First Landing Expedition; First Siblings; The Neosyne.

Onboard: Security, unranked.

Rank: N/A.

AKA: "Golem"

The First Mnemosyne; layered by Dr. Leticia Lopez, Dr. Thomas ODoyle and Dr. Ralf Hounds.

Sibling to Faye "Mutt" Thomas and Laura "Runt" Orouli.

Part of the First Expedition: Gavin is the first Mnemosyne and the second Human to have set foot on Rhyldan.

"Who... Where...?"

"Who are you?"

"Who are we?" - Gavins first words, as he Woke Up.

Status: Alive.

1704.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Dr. Stephanie Burroughs
1704.description:
Human Doctor.
Mission Specialist. (Agrology)

Onboard: Systems - Hydroponics Assistant.

Rank: Doctor.

AKA: N/A

From California, US. Social butterfly and a gwyn. Tall, well-proportioned. Shoulder-length blond hair.

Caught the eye of just about every man onboard the Star at some point. Rumored to have given Gavin his first "experience."

Stephanie was suspected of manipulating the male doctors to authorize a new cloned body for her.

Stephanie has a brilliant mind, once she learns to focus. Discovered most of the plants on Rhldyan.

Human MnemoTech.
Mnemosye Team; Neosyne Layer.

Rank: Doctor.

Argentine; Neuroscientist, Universidad de Buenos Aires. Twice Nobel nominee.

Along Dr. Thomas Doyle and Dr. Ralf Hounds, layered Gavin "Golem" Stones.

First Council Member - Mnemosyne Dept.

"May it be an evening star shines bright upon you." - Letty to Puppy, as he boarded the Odgerel before the First Landing.

Status: Alive.

FTO: "Adrenaline", by Gavin Rossdale (Song).

1706.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Dr. Itzka Kourailen
1706.description:

Psychiatry; Neosynes Psycho.

Onboard: Med - Psychiatry.

Rank: Doctor.

AKA: "Doc".

Doc was Gavins psycho, and deemed him Fit for Human Interaction.

"Who knows? Guess well have to find out." - Doc to Gavin, after Gavin asked: "Am I human?"

Status: Alive.

FTO: Cohibas (Drug).

1707.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Dr. Danio Jenkins
1707.description:
Human Cloner
Cloning; Chief.

Onboard: Cloning; Chief.

Rank: Doctor.

AKA: The Necromancer.

USA; Bioscientists, MIT Course VII. Onboard the Star, Dr. Jenkins lead the Cloning Team.

"DNA is like Poetry: it must be." - Dr. Jenkins, while handing Gavins Wake Up code to Letty.

Status: Starfell.

FTO: String Quartet No. 16, by Ludwig van Beethoven (Music).

1708.name: StarCast (1st Ed.): Anne Tolley
1708.description:
Human Engineer
Chief; Expert; Dark Matter Engines.

Onboard: Engineering; Chief.

Rank: Chief.

AKA: "Crazy Annie".

New Zealand. Graduated from the Faculty of Engineering, University of Auckland; former professor at MIT. Short, athletic, dark-skinned.

Anne was a bit eccentric and preferred the company of machines over people. She was rarely found outside of Engineering; she treated the ship as if it were her offspring.

"No sir, I can still save her!" - Anne to Kjell, shortly before the Northern Star exploded.

Status: Starfell

1710.description:
Human MnemoTech.
Mnemosye Team; Champion of the Arts.

Onboard: Mnemosyne Team.

Rank: Doctor.

AKA: Tunes, for his love of music and songs.

German; Doctorate in Cognitive Science from the University of Hamburg; average build, dark hair, brown eyes, excitable.

Long term partner of Dr. Karl Fleischer, together they layered the memories of Faye Mutt Thomas, the second ever Mnemosyne created.

After Starfell, he successfully argued for resources to be spent supporting the promotion of music and song. 

Music will help us heal. It cannot be considered an unnecessary waste of resources. - Kurt, before the OWON Council.

Status: Alive. 

FTO: The Ultimate Eurovision Mega Compilation (Vids).
